<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2583&amp;p=20707#p20707"><![CDATA[
You don't want CreateMDIWindow if you want the "child window" to appear on its own on the desktop - you want CreateWindow with the appropriate flags (parent window, frame type, whether or not it's on the taskbar, etc.).<br /><br />If you want to see how it's done in C, take a look at Nintendulator's source code - this is exactly what I do for the debugger windows.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Fri Dec 29, 2006 6:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
